				<div class="postbody">
				Some total newbie questions here because I only got in three days play time before beta closed.
<br />

<br />
Ok, I understand how weapon skills go up (just like EQ).  What I'm not sure about is if you can get new weapon skills, and if so how?
<br />

<br />
From the WoW site, I see this for Priests:
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Allowable Weapons: One-Handed Maces, Daggers, Staves, Wands </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
However, as a dwarf priest, I only had a skill listed for Maces (maybe wands, I forget cuz I never found a wand that was useable).  I'm positive that Staves were not in my skill list, and I ran accross a few staves that kicked butt which I would have loved to equip.
<br />

<br />
Same goes for shields.  I was using a one-handed mace, and I looted several shields (duh, can't a priest equip a shield?) and I couldn't equip them.  Is there a shield skill or was I just looting shields too high for me?
<br />

<br />
Same for two-handed mace.  Every one I saw was red (can't equip).  I don't even think there is a two handed mace skill, but either way I couldn't even go to a newbie vendor and buy the smallest 2 handed mace for level 1 characters when I was 10th level.  <span style="font-style: italic">/edit: nevermind on this one, I dropped my retardery for two seconds to read the "one-handed maces" in the skills listed above).</span>
<br />

<br />
I've looked here and there on different sites but they all seem to have different information on skills (because stuff changed alot during beta).  It seems like most of the sites have been focusing on talent information and not keeping their skill information up to date.
<br />

<br />
Any help would be appreciated.  Think I'm still gonna go Dwarf Priest for retail.  Night Elf priest looks nice as well, but I can't be a tallard and show my face to the world, so dorf it is.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
