			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				I was a priest, played 7 diff ones during beta.  Basically you start out with the maces and wands.  You must train at a weapons master.  Not every master in each main city will train all though.
<br />

<br />
For dwarf you can train the staves in Stormwind by taking the tram there.  It will cost you 10sp.  They've moved the trainer 3 times now.  He was in the mage district, then in the Old Town (rogue area) now he seems to be in a weapons shop in the Trade district.  Shields no go =( dumb but a no go not unless it is a much much much higher lvl ability I've never seen it.  Daggers for dwarf I'm not sure, I never saw the option pop up on either the weaponsmaster in Ironforge nor in Stormwind, I tried.  Could possibly be a race thing?  not sure with that.
<br />

<br />
On the Horde side, daggers are easy.  Train at the WM in Orgrimarr.  Staves is a bitch because it's all the way in Thunderbluff which can get tricky when you are really really newbie and want that damn staff ability.  he is up outside the weapons shop on the lower lift there.
<br />

<br />
I've used all the weapons available and I would really say train in them all when you can and skill them up!  Never know when something really great you could use might come along.  It was also really cool as an undead priest wearing a vest/pants instead of the robe and packing a dagger.  Kinda throws off people immediately knowing you are a caster at first by appearance.  <img src="images/smiles/razz.gif" alt="razz" border="0" /><br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
